==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trundlehead
<hw>Trun"dle*head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gearing)</fld> <def>One of the disks forming the ends of a lantern
wheel or pinion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The drumhead of a capstan; especially, the drumhead
of the lower of two capstans on the sane axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trundletail</ent>⟦br⟧
